outline.text: Pancakes Ingredients: 1 cup all-purpose flour
Instructions: In a bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.
In another bowl, combine buttermilk, egg, melted butter, and vanilla extract.
Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.
Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and lightly grease it.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter onto the skillet for each pancake.
Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown.
Serve with syrup and your favorite toppings.
Scrambled Eggs Ingredients: 4 large eggs
Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions: In a bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, salt, and pepper.
Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat and melt the butter.
Pour the egg mixture into the skillet.
Cook, stirring gently, until the eggs are set but still soft.
Serve immediately.
French Toast Ingredients: 4 slices of bread
Instructions: In a shallow dish, whisk together eggs, milk, vanilla extract, and cinnamon.
Dip each slice of bread into the egg mixture, coating both sides.
Cook the bread slices until golden brown on both sides.
Serve with syrup and powdered sugar.
Smoothie Bowl Ingredients: 1 banana
1/2 cup Greek yogurt
Toppings: granola, fresh fruit, nuts, seeds
Instructions: In a blender, combine banana, frozen berries, Greek yogurt, and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into a bowl and top with granola, fresh fruit, nuts, and seeds.
Avocado Toast Ingredients: 2 slices of bread
Optional toppings: cherry tomatoes, red pepper flakes, poached egg
Instructions: Toast the bread slices.
Mash the avocado in a bowl and season with salt and pepper.
Spread the mashed avocado on the toast.
Add optional toppings if desired.
Breakfast Burrito Ingredients: 2 large eggs
Salsa for serving
Add cheese, sausage or bacon, bell pepper, and onion to the eggs.
Cook until the eggs are set and the vegetables are tender.
Place the egg mixture in the center of the tortilla and roll it up.
Serve with salsa.
Oatmeal Ingredients: 1 cup rolled oats
Toppings: fresh fruit, nuts, honey, cinnamon
Instructions: In a saucepan, bring water or milk to a boil.
Add oats and salt, reduce heat to low, and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and let sit for a few minutes.
Serve with your favorite toppings.
Yogurt Parfait Ingredients: 1 cup Greek yogurt
Honey for drizzling
Instructions: In a glass or bowl, layer Greek yogurt, granola, and fresh berries.
Drizzle with honey.
Repeat layers if desired.
Breakfast Sandwich Ingredients: 1 English muffin, split and toasted
Instructions: Cook the egg in a skillet over medium heat, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Place the cheese on top of the egg to melt.
Assemble the sandwich with the egg, cheese, and ham or bacon between the English
muffin halves. Chia Pudding Ingredients: 1/4 cup chia seeds
Toppings: fresh fruit, nuts, coconut flakes
extract. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Stir well before serving and top with your favorite toppings.
Breakfast Quesadilla Ingredients: 1 large flour tortilla
Add cheese, sausage or bacon, and bell pepper to the eggs.
Cook in the skillet until the tortilla is golden brown and crispy.
Banana Bread Ingredients: 3 ripe bananas, mashed
Pinch of salt
Instructions: Preheat oven to 350째F (175째C).
In a bowl, mix mashed bananas and melted butter.
Add sugar, beaten egg, and vanilla extract, and mix well.
Stir in baking soda, salt, and flour until just combined.
Pour the batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake for 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Let cool before slicing.
Breakfast Tacos Ingredients: 2 large eggs
Add cheese, sausage or bacon, onions and bell pepper to the eggs.
Divide the egg mixture between the tortillas.
Granola Bars Ingredients: 2 cups rolled oats
extract. Press the mixture into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool before cutting into bars.
Smoothie Ingredients: 1 banana
Instructions: In a blender, combine banana, frozen berries, Greek yogurt, milk, and honey.
Breakfast Pizza Ingredients: 1 pre-made pizza crust
Instructions: Preheat oven to 425째F (220째C).
Spread marinara sauce over the pizza crust.
Sprinkle mozzarella cheese on top.
Crack the eggs onto the pizza.
Add sausage or bacon and bell pepper.
Bake for 10-12 minutes or until the eggs are set and the cheese is melted.
Muffins Ingredients: 2 cups all-purpose flour
Instructions: Preheat oven to 375째F (190째C).
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
In another bowl, combine milk, vegetable oil, egg, and vanilla extract.
Fold in the berries.
Divide the batter evenly among a greased muffin tin.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.
Let cool before serving.
Breakfast Casserole Ingredients: 6 large eggs
In a bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, salt, and pepper.
Stir in cheese, sausage or bacon, bell pepper, and onion.
Pour the mixture into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 30-35 minutes or until the eggs are set.
Let cool slightly before serving.
Bagel with Cream Cheese Ingredients: 1 bagel, sliced and toasted
Optional toppings: smoked salmon, capers, red onion, tomato slices
Instructions: Spread cream cheese on each half of the toasted bagel.
Breakfast Skillet Ingredients: 2 large eggs
Instructions: Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add potatoes, bell pepper, and onion, and cook until tender.
Add sausage or bacon and cook until heated through.
Make two wells in the mixture and crack an egg into each well.
Cover and cook until the eggs are set.
Season with salt and pepper.
Breakfast Bowl Ingredients: 1/2 cup cooked quinoa
Instructions: In a bowl, combine quinoa, black beans, avocado, and cherry tomatoes.
Top with the poached or fried egg.
Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
Breakfast Croissant Ingredients: 1 croissant, sliced in half
Assemble the sandwich with the egg, cheese, and ham or bacon between the
croissant halves. Serve immediately.
Breakfast Frittata Ingredients: 6 large eggs
Stir in cheese, bell pepper, onion, and sausage or bacon.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Pour the egg mixture into the skillet and cook until the edges are set.
Let cool slightly before slicing and serving.
Breakfast Bagel Sandwich Ingredients: 1 bagel, sliced and toasted
Assemble the sandwich with the egg, cheese, and ham or bacon between the bagel
halves. Serve immediately.
Overnight Oats Ingredients: 1/2 cup rolled oats
Toppings: fresh fruit, nuts, seeds
extract. Stir well, cover, and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, stir again and add your favorite toppings.
Egg Muffins Ingredients: 6 large eggs
Stir in bell pepper, spinach, and cheese.
Pour the mixture into a greased muffin tin.
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the eggs are set.
Let cool before removing from the tin.
Apple Peanut Butter Sandwiches Ingredients: 1 apple, cored and sliced into rings
Optional toppings: granola, raisins, coconut flakes
Instructions: Spread peanut butter on one side of each apple ring.
Sandwich two apple rings together with the peanut butter sides facing in.
Protein Smoothie Ingredients: 1 banana
Instructions:
In a blender, combine banana, Greek yogurt, almond milk, protein powder, and
peanut butter. Blend until smooth.
Cottage Cheese and Fruit Ingredients: 1 cup cottage cheese
Instructions: In a bowl, combine cottage cheese and fresh berries.
Veggie Wrap Ingredients: 1 large whole wheat tortilla
Instructions: Spread hummus on the tortilla.
Layer with shredded carrots, cucumber, spinach, and bell pepper.
Roll up the tortilla tightly.
Slice in half and serve.
Almond Butter Banana Toast Ingredients: 2 slices whole grain bread, toasted
Instructions: Spread almond butter on the toasted bread.
Top with banana slices and sprinkle with chia seeds.
Greek Yogurt with Honey and Nuts Ingredients: 1 cup Greek yogurt
Instructions: In a bowl, combine Greek yogurt and honey.
Top with mixed nuts.
Avocado and Egg Toast Ingredients: 2 slices whole grain bread, toasted
Crushed red pepper flakes to taste
Instructions: Mash the avocado and spread it on the toasted bread.
Season with crushed red pepper flakes + salt and pepper.
Quinoa Breakfast Bowl Ingredients: 1/2 cup cooked quinoa
Instructions: In a bowl, combine cooked quinoa, avocado, and cherry tomatoes.
Berry and Spinach Smoothie Ingredients: 1/2 cup frozen berries
Instructions: In a blender, combine frozen berries, spinach, Greek yogurt, almond milk, and honey.
Fruit and Nut Bars Ingredients: 1 cup dates, pitted
Instructions: In a food processor, combine dates, mixed nuts, dried fruit, and honey.
Process until the mixture comes together.
Press the mixture into a greased baking dish.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before cutting into bars.
Store in an airtight container.
Peanut Butter and Banana Smoothie Ingredients: 1 banana
Instructions: In a blender, combine banana, Greek yogurt, almond milk, peanut butter, and honey.
Cottage Cheese and Veggie Bowl Ingredients: 1 cup cottage cheese
Instructions: In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, and bell pepper.
Almond Butter and Apple Slices Ingredients: 1 apple, sliced
Instructions: Spread almond butter on each apple slice.
